I've found all the code related to project creation limits and deletion. Here's the complete breakdown:

---

## 1. PROJECT CREATION LIMITS / SANDBOX PROJECT CAPS

**File**: `/Users/devs/Downloads/Apollo/apps/web/app/api/projects/route.ts`

**The Limit**: Max 1 sandbox project per user (enforced in the POST handler, lines 53-72)

```typescript
// Sandbox project limit: max 1 sandbox project per user
const { count: sandboxCount } = await supabase
  .from("projects")
  .select("id", { count: "exact", head: true })
  .eq("user_id", user.id)
  .eq("status", "sandbox");

if ((sandboxCount ?? 0) >= 1) {
  return NextResponse.json(
    {
      error: {
        code: "SANDBOX_LIMIT",
        message:
          "You already have a sandbox project. Purchase a licence to unlock it, or delete it to start a new one.",
        action: "purchase_licence",
      },
    },
    { status: 402 }
  );
}
```

**Error Response**: 402 Payment Required with `SANDBOX_LIMIT` code

**Pricing Config**: `/Users/devs/Downloads/Apollo/apps/web/lib/pricing/config.ts` (line 35)
- Sandbox plan includes "1 sandbox project" as a feature
- Sandbox phases limited to [0, 1, 2] (Orientation, Front Matter, Introduction)

---

## 2. PROJECT DELETION

### API Route
**File**: `/Users/devs/Downloads/Apollo/apps/web/app/api/projects/[id]/route.ts`

**DELETE Handler** (lines 93-139):
```typescript
export async function DELETE(
  _request: NextRequest,
  { params }: { params: Promise<{ id: string }> }
) {
  try {
    const authResult = await getAuthenticatedUser();
    if (!authResult) return unauthorised();

    const { id } = await params;
    const supabase = await createServerSupabaseClient();

    // Verify project exists and belongs to user (RLS handles ownership)
    const { data: project, error: fetchError } = await supabase
      .from("projects")
      .select("id")
      .eq("id", id)
      .single();

    if (fetchError || !project) {
      return notFound("Project not found");
    }

    // Clean R2 objects for this project (9.9)
    try {
      await deleteR2Prefix(`projects/${id}/`);
    } catch (r2Err) {
      console.error(`R2 cleanup failed for project ${id}:`, r2Err);
      // Continue with DB deletion even if R2 cleanup fails
    }

    // Hard-delete project (CASCADE handles child tables + audit_log)
    const { error: deleteError } = await supabase
      .from("projects")
      .delete()
      .eq("id", id);

    if (deleteError) {
      console.error("Failed to delete project:", deleteError);
      return internalError("Failed to delete project");
    }

    return NextResponse.json({ data: { deleted: true } });
  } catch (err) {
    console.error("Unexpected error in DELETE /api/projects/[id]:", err);
    return internalError();
  }
}
```

**Key Points**:
- RLS (Row-Level Security) handles ownership verification
- Cleans R2 storage bucket prefix `projects/{id}/` before DB deletion
- Uses CASCADE to delete all child records (sections, citations, analyses, figures, compilations, conversations, audit logs)
- Returns success JSON on completion

### UI Component
**File**: `/Users/devs/Downloads/Apollo/components/project/delete-project-button.tsx`

```typescript
export function DeleteProjectButton({
  projectId,
  projectTitle,
}: DeleteProjectButtonProps) {
  const [confirming, setConfirming] = useState(false);
  const [deleting, setDeleting] = useState(false);
  const router = useRouter();

  async function handleDelete() {
    setDeleting(true);
    try {
      const resp = await fetch(`/api/projects/${projectId}`, {
        method: "DELETE",
      });
      if (resp.ok) {
        router.refresh();
      }
    } finally {
      setDeleting(false);
      setConfirming(false);
    }
  }

  if (confirming) {
    return (
      <div
        className="flex items-center gap-2"
        onClick={(e) => e.preventDefault()}
      >
        <span className="text-xs text-destructive">Delete?</span>
        <button
          type="button"
          onClick={(e) => {
            e.preventDefault();
            void handleDelete();
          }}
          disabled={deleting}
          className="rounded px-2 py-0.5 text-xs font-medium bg-destructive text-destructive-foreground hover:bg-destructive/90 disabled:opacity-50"
        >
          {deleting ? "..." : "Yes"}
        </button>
        <button
          type="button"
          onClick={(e) => {
            e.preventDefault();
            setConfirming(false);
          }}
          className="rounded px-2 py-0.5 text-xs font-medium bg-muted text-muted-foreground hover:bg-muted/80"
        >
          No
        </button>
      </div>
    );
  }

  return (
    <button
      type="button"
      onClick={(e) => {
        e.preventDefault();
        setConfirming(true);
      }}
      className="rounded p-1 text-muted-foreground/50 hover:text-destructive hover:bg-destructive/10 transition-colors"
      title={`Delete ${projectTitle}`}
    >
      <Trash2 className="h-4 w-4" />
    </button>
  );
}
```

**Features**:
- Two-stage confirmation (click icon → confirm "Delete?" → click "Yes")
- Trash icon that turns red on hover
- Loading state while deletion in progress
- Refreshes router on successful deletion

### UI Integration
**File**: `/Users/devs/Downloads/Apollo/app/(dashboard)/projects/project-card.tsx` (lines 58-61)

The `DeleteProjectButton` is integrated into each project card in the projects listing page.

---

## 3. PROJECT TYPE / STATUS FIELD

**File**: `/Users/devs/Downloads/Apollo/apps/web/lib/types/database.ts`

```typescript
export type ProjectStatus = "sandbox" | "licensed" | "completed" | "archived";

export interface Project {
  id: string;
  user_id: string;
  organisation_id: string | null;
  status: ProjectStatus;
  license_id: string | null;
  title: string;
  synopsis_text: string | null;
  study_type: string | null;
  university_type: UniversityType | null;
  metadata_json: ProjectMetadata;
  current_phase: number;
  phases_completed: number[];
  analysis_plan_json: Record<string, unknown>[];
  analysis_plan_status: AnalysisPlanStatus;
  created_at: string;
  updated_at: string;
}
```

**Project Status Values**:
- `"sandbox"` — Free trial project (phases 0-2 only, no license required)
- `"licensed"` — Active licensed project (full 12-phase access)
- `"completed"` — Finished thesis project
- `"archived"` — Hidden from projects list (soft deletion equivalent)

**Project Lifecycle**:
1. Created as `"sandbox"` (no license attached)
2. Transitions to `"licensed"` when license is attached (Phase 1→2 gate requires this)
3. Can be marked `"completed"` when thesis is finalized
4. Can be set to `"archived"` to hide from view
5. Can be hard-deleted via DELETE API route

---

## 4. PROJECT CREATION (POST Handler)

**File**: `/Users/devs/Downloads/Apollo/apps/web/app/api/projects/route.ts` (lines 36-98)

```typescript
export async function POST(request: NextRequest) {
  try {
    const authResult = await getAuthenticatedUser();
    if (!authResult) return unauthorised();

    const body = await request.json();
    const parsed = projectCreateSchema.safeParse(body);

    if (!parsed.success) {
      return validationError("Invalid project data", {
        issues: parsed.error.flatten().fieldErrors,
      });
    }

    const { user } = authResult;
    const supabase = await createServerSupabaseClient();

    // Sandbox project limit: max 1 sandbox project per user
    const { count: sandboxCount } = await supabase
      .from("projects")
      .select("id", { count: "exact", head: true })
      .eq("user_id", user.id)
      .eq("status", "sandbox");

    if ((sandboxCount ?? 0) >= 1) {
      return NextResponse.json(
        {
          error: {
            code: "SANDBOX_LIMIT",
            message:
              "You already have a sandbox project. Purchase a licence to unlock it, or delete it to start a new one.",
            action: "purchase_licence",
          },
        },
        { status: 402 }
      );
    }

    const { data: project, error } = await supabase
      .from("projects")
      .insert({
        user_id: user.id,
        title: parsed.data.title,
        university_type: parsed.data.university_type,
        status: "sandbox",
        current_phase: 0,
        metadata_json: {},
        phases_completed: [],
      })
      .select("*")
      .single();

    if (error) {
      console.error("Failed to create project:", error);
      return internalError("Failed to create project");
    }

    return NextResponse.json({ data: project }, { status: 201 });
  } catch (err) {
    console.error("Unexpected error in POST /api/projects:", err);
    return internalError();
  }
}
```

**Schema Validation** (`projectCreateSchema`):
```typescript
export const projectCreateSchema = z.object({
  title: z.string().min(1, "Title is required").max(500),
  university_type: z.enum(["wbuhs", "ssuhs", "generic"]),
});
```

**Initialization**:
- All projects start with `status: "sandbox"`
- `current_phase: 0` (Orientation)
- `phases_completed: []`
- `metadata_json: {}`

---

## 5. GET Handler (Fetch User Projects)

**File**: `/Users/devs/Downloads/Apollo/apps/web/app/api/projects/route.ts` (lines 11-34)

Fetches all projects for authenticated user, ordered by `updated_at` descending.

---

## Key Architectural Notes

1. **Sandbox Cap Enforcement**: Single point of control in POST `/api/projects` route
2. **Deletion Cleanup**: Two-phase (R2 storage first, then DB cascade delete)
3. **Soft Delete via Status**: Projects can be marked `"archived"` instead of hard-deleted (projects list filters them out)
4. **RLS Protection**: All queries filtered by `user_id` via Supabase RLS policies
5. **Idempotent Messaging**: Error message on sandbox limit suggests both "purchase licence" and "delete it" actions
6. **No "Hard Reset"**: Deletion is permanent; `ResetProjectButton` (separate feature) resets to Phase 0 but keeps project

